land in the 19th century, played with an oval ball by two teams of 15 players. The Rugby World Cup is the sport's premier international competition with dominant nations like New Zealand and South Africa.", "Baseball is a bat-and-ball sport played between two teams of nine players on a diamond-shaped field. Known as America's pastime, the World Series is the championship of Major League Baseball in the United States and Canada."], "scores": [0.7188226155573834, 0.6765271087260962, 0.6474047520348032, 0.6400879185938845, 0.6158545439736317], "model_name": "bge-base", "document_ids": ["Soccer", "Cricket", "Basketball", "Rugby", "Baseball"]}}